January 29, 2007 12:29Guests and users operating and using the software at the scene.Photo by Dai Lan, Reporter of People's Daily OnlinePeople's Daily Online, Urumqi, January 29, Reporters Wang Huimin, Dai Lan. The Xinjiang's Chinese, Uygur, Kazak, Kyrgyz Language Version Office Software Product (Yongzhong 2007 edition) press release was grandly held in Urumqi in recent days.The successful development of the product filled the gap of the lack of Uygur, Kazak, and Kyrgyz language office software in Xinjiang and is beneficial to the promotion of the building of e-government and the development of informatization in Xinjiang.According to the account of the Xinjiang Technical Institute of Physics and Chemistry of the Chinese Academy of Sciences, this office product uses all Uygur language operation interface and on-line support system. It contains interface layout that conforms to the writing style of from right to left of the Uygur, Kazak, and Kyrgyz languages. Users can choose functions of changing new line according to the syllables and automatic lengthening of alphabets to achieve a more artistic effect in editing and typesetting of files in the Uygur, Kazak, and Kyrgyz languages.